profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
Dr. Bruce Idelkope practices neurology at High Country Healthcare Frisco where he treats post-stroke patients needing rehabilitation, traumatic brain injuries and other concussive syndromes, and those affected by multiple sclerosis, among other conditions. His schedule includes several days each month locally with follow-up consultative care as needed.

Dr. Idelkope first became part of the Summit County community in the early 1990s to pursue recreational passions. Later, he became acquainted with Colorado’s health care community while addressing health developments for a friend and then a family member.

“I was so impressed with the high caliber of care we received from everyone we encountered while moving through our cycle of care that I knew I wanted to be a part of it,” he says. “Since launching a practice here, I have met some of the most wonderful, capable people. This is a population that is truly dedicated to taking ownership of their health which is simply not true of other communities.”

Dr. Idelkope recently delivered the keynote address at a conference for the Colorado Brain Injury Alliance at St. Anthony’s Summit Medical Center entitled, “The Long Term Effects of Mild TBI; Often Under-Recognized and Under Treated Today.”

Beyond his role with High Country Healthcare, Dr. Idelkope currently serves as Vice President of the Minneapolis Clinic of Neurology, the nation’s largest, private neurology practice with more than 35 health care providers on staff. For more than 20 years he has directed their Rehabilitative Services Branch. He is also the physician of record related to concussive syndromes for the Minnesota Vikings.

Dr. Idelkope is board certified from the American Academy of Psychiatry and Neurology and is a member of the American Academy of Neurology, the American Neurological Society and the American Society of Neurorehabilitation, among other professional organizations.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
Dr. Michael Ellman has recently joined Panorama Orthopedics & Spine Center’s sports medicine team. Dr. Ellman, most recently with the Steadman Clinic in Vail, is a board-eligible orthopedic surgeon specializing in hip, knee and shoulder injuries.

Dr. Ellman brings with him unique experience in repairing and reconstructing hip labral tears, which involves the ring of cartilage that goes around the hip socket. Hockey, soccer and football players, as well as golfers, runners, and ballet dancers, are at higher risk for developing hip labral tears. In the past, many of these injuries went undiagnosed and untreated, but thanks to new techniques used by a select group of doctors – including Dr. Ellman – physicians are able to successfully treat this injury.

“My goal is deliver the highest-quality care to each and every patient from all walks of life, from weekend warriors to professional athletes,” he said. “I do my best to help patients achieve their goals, whatever that may be.”

Dr. Ellman completed his orthopedic training at Rush University Medical Center in Chicago. As a resident, he published more than 40 research studies focused on cartilage biology, biochemical pathways involved in osteoarthritis, and orthopedic surgical techniques,  and was awarded the American Academy of Orthopaedics Baxter Healthcare Scholarship for his research in hip arthroscopy. Dr. Ellman also participated in sports team coverage for several teams, including the Chicago Bulls, Chicago White Sox, DePaul University’s men’s and women’s soccer teams and multiple high school football teams.

Following residency, Dr. Ellman went on to complete a one-year fellowship in sports medicine and hip arthroscopy at the Steadman Clinic. During this time, he trained under world-renowned surgeons in the field of hip, knee, and shoulder arthroscopy, and worked as a consulting team physician for the U.S. Olympic Ski and Snowboard teams. He traveled to Chile and Austria as the head team physician for the alpine and boardercross teams and covered events at Copper Mountain, Vail and Beaver Creek.

Outside of work, Dr. Ellman enjoys spending time with his wife and baby daughter, You’ll also find him cheering on the Michigan Wolverines, as well as participating in a variety of outdoor activities and sports, including basketball, hiking, and skiing.

practices.name: Colorado Pain Practice, PLLC
practices.description:
Colorado Pain provides patients with education, compassion, and quality care. We treat each patient like we would our own mom and dad. We provide this care to patients with acute or chronic pain conditions as a result of surgical procedure, injury, disease or disorder. We offer pain management services including state-of-the-art diagnostic imaging and testing, comprehensive evaluation, friendly consultation, effective treatment and follow-up care. Our award winning physicians, chiropractors, physician’s assistants and nurse practitioners deliver the highest quality care in the mile high city.

Dr. Jason Krutsch, Dr. Robert Moghim, Dr. Paul Lynch, and Dr. Tory McJunkin, are among the best in the country at treating rapidly evolving pain management services and treatments. Colorado Pain’s services are further enhanced by affiliations with several top specialists in a variety of fields including: pain management, diagnostic laboratories, and complete hospital facilities and services.

Our cutting edge approach to pain management treatments include a variety of acute and chronic pain conditions such as herniated (or “ruptured”) discs and complex regional pain syndrome (RSD, Causalgia). We offer state-of-the-art diagnostic and pain treatment services that are further enhanced through relationships with other award winning specialists and hospital affiliations.

An interdisciplinary approach to pain management is essential to our mission. We include a comprehensive evaluation for all of our patients. Through this exam, we look at the physical, functional, emotional and psychological needs of the patient.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
Dr. Robert Moghim is a board certified medical clinician and practice leader. His strong leadership abilities were first recognized in high school and college where he excelled in soccer and achieved U.S. National Youth Soccer Team recognition, All American Honors, and NCAA Final Four achievements with the top ranked Division I Duke Blue Devils (Duke University). Immediately after graduating with honors from Duke University, Dr. Moghim attended the University Of Tennessee College Of Medicine, where he received his medical degree. Shortly after, he did his residency at The University of Colorado Health Science Center and completed the board certification process shortly thereafter.

Dr. Moghim is the co-founder of Colorado Pain, part of a multi-state practice with over seven clinics, four surgery centers, and average monthly new patient visits over 1,200 patients per month.

Dr. Moghim is an esteemed pain specialist with over ten years of comprehensive clinical practice experience. He is also the founder of Horizon Anesthesia and Pain Consultants, a Northern California practice, that remains one of the premier service providers in the area for the past ten years.

Dr. Moghim has performed over 7,000 interventional procedures with no malpractice claims and a clean record with the National Practitioner Data Bank (NPDB). He has also earned top rankings at Healthgrades.com as a 5-star provider. Dr. Moghim is also a Level 2 accredited workmen’s compensation provider certified by the state of Colorado.

Pain Doctor CertifiedIn addition to be being a top pain clinician, Dr. Moghim founded Onyx M.D., a nationwide physician staffing company with corporate offices located in Denver, CO and Dallas, TX. The company has established a national staffing presence in all 50 states, thereby creating revenue growth that puts it on track to become one of the largest privately-held physician services company in the United States. Most recently, Onyx M.D. was recognized in the new Topgrading 3rd Edition book released on August 16th, 2012, as a true Topgrading organization. To augment the service aspect of the company, Dr. Moghim implemented an employee-directed community outreach program called S.C.O.P.E., an acronym for: Service, Community, Outreach, Purpose, and Excellence. The program allows the employees of Onyx M.D. to submit a charity for the company to support. In its first year, S.C.O.P.E. donated over $7,000 to twelve different local charities.

Dr. Robert Moghim is also an avid reader with interests in U.S. healthcare policy and politics. He also writes and contributes articles for the Onyx M.D. blog (onyxmd.com/blog). Sharing his perspective on controversial healthcare policies, Dr. Moghim has acquired a strong following and garnered much attention through his writing. He has expanded his areas of focus to alternative treatment option research in the field of pain medicine. With Colorado ranking as one of the worst prescription drug abuse states in the nation, Dr. Moghim has set out to help alter this epidemic that has killed more people than car accidents annually.

Dr. Stewart K. Weinerman attended medical school and residency at The New York Medical College in Valhala, New York. He served as Chief Resident in the largest of the New York City trauma hospitals.

He moved to Denver in 1986, and has been an integral part of Colorado Orthopedic Consultants since. He has served as chairman of the department of orthopedic surgery for 4 years, in addition to serving as associate professor of orthopedics at College of Osteopathic Medicine of the Pacific and the University of Colorado. He is the team physician for Gateway High School and is a member of the Arthroscopy Association of North America as well as the American Academy of Orthopedic Surgeons.

Dr. Weinerman’s other interests especially include shoulder and knee injury, sports medicine, and trauma, cartilage replacement/repair.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
Dr. Resig moved to Denver and joined Denver-Vail Orthopedics, P.C. in 2004. He is board certified through the American Board of Orthopaedic Surgeons. Dr. Resig specializes in complex conditions of the lower extremity with a focus in foot and ankle as well as hip and knee joint replacement. Dr. Resig utilizes many of the most advanced technologies available in orthopedics, including robotic knee surgery, anterior minimally invasive hip replacement and custom ankle replacement.

Dr. Resig pursued his undergraduate degree at the University of Wisconsin, graduating with distinction. He received his medical degree and completed his orthopedic residency at the University of Minnesota Medical School. After completing his residency he pursued fellowship training at the Adidas Sports Medicine Institute and then continued his fellowship training in orthopedic foot & ankle surgery at the University of Auckland, New Zealand.

Dr. Resig is currently the Chairman of Orthopedic Surgery at Sky Ridge Medical Center. He enjoys competitive sports and is familiar with the frustrations an injury can cause. Dr. Resig hopes that the use of the newest technological advances in orthopedics can give his patients the best outcomes with a quicker recovery.

Dr. Resig recently completed an Ironman triathlon and he has run multiple marathons but his greatest joy comes from being a devoted husband and father of two girls.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio: I grew up in Southern California, and I have always enjoyed a very active and healthy lifestyle. I grew up playing soccer, skiing and spending time at the beach. As a child, it always bothered me so much when I was either injured so I could not play soccer, or I was sick and could not do the things that I so much enjoyed. This is really what drove me into Pediatrics, and I feel honored to be a part of families' lives. Life can be so joyful when we are well and our children are well. I love educating parents and children about maintaining health and preventing illness and injury, so that they can enjoy the thrills that life has to offer. My two daughters have strengthened this drive, as they have taught me first-hand about the pleasures as well as difficulties of parenthood.

profile.title: DO
profile.bio:
I am a board-certified family practice physician. I practice full spectrum family practice for all ages. I focus on preventive care with health and lifestyle as a priority. I also treat acute and chronic illness and injury. Osteopathic manipulation is approximately 5-10% of my practice and I would gladly expand these hands on services.
 
I performed my residency training at the Colorado Springs Osteopathic Foundation with emphasis on sports medicine, manipulative treatment, and nutritional/alternative health. I strive to be well connected to top specialists in all areas of medicine and to a variety of alternative healthcare practitioners so that I can be an advocate for your care in any area that might help you feel your best.
 
I attended medical school at the University of North Texas Health Science Center (UNTHSC) in Fort Worth, Texas. As a second-year student, I was awarded an Undergraduate Teaching Fellowship in manipulative medicine and taught at UNTHSC for one year while completing my medical education.
 
Prior to attending medical school, I had a successful career as a technical writer for telephony and oil companies in Texas. I attended graduate school to study sports nutrition. I also owned and operated Healthy Kneads Therapeutic Massage for six years.

profile.bio:
Dr. Nations graduated from the University of South Alabama College of Medicine. He completed his residency at North Memorial Medical Center, University of Minnesota, Department of Family Practice.

Dr. Nations practices the full spectrum of family medicine and urgent care, with particular interest in pediatrics, sports injuries and dermatologic conditions.

Dr. Nations has been practicing family medicine in Summit County for 13 years.  He especially enjoys the long-term relationships he has developed after more than a decade of sharing in the lives of Summit County residents, as well as meeting people from every continent (even Antarctica!) on earth.

Dr. Nations enjoys snowmobiling, kiteboarding, motorcycles  and general aviation.  But most of all, he likes to spend time with his family: his wife Michelle and his children Megan (11), Maddie (8), Haley (6) and Gavin (2).

Dr. Nations sees patients at High Country Healthcare Breckenridge.
